article.headline: Brown 70, Hartford 60
article.story: HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) -- Damon Huffman scored 16 points and freshman Scott Friske added a career high 12 points to lead Brown University to a 70-60 win over the University of Hartford on Wednesday. The Bears connected on 29 of 30 shots from the free throw line. Huffman scored 12 of his 16 points, and Friske netted 10 of his 12 points. After the first 10 minutes, Brown held its biggest lead when Chris Skrelja's layup made it 21-5. Hartford responded with 16 unanswered points over the next five minutes to tie the game at 21-21. David Ruffin had five points during the stretch. After trading baskets, Hartford took its only lead of the game, 27-25, on a layup by Kenny Adeleke with less than three minutes in the half. The Bears led for the entire second half, leading by as many as 13 points, 54-41 on a lay-up by James Daniels. Hartford pulled to within two points of the Bears, 60-58, on a jump shot by Ruffian with 6:32 left to play. Huffman answered by connecting on two free throws with 4:48 remaining, and the Bears were never challenged for the remainder of the game.
